    "markdown": "---\ntitle: \"ex11. Causal (Same backend, CRP Backend) - Cauchy/Laplace\"\n---\n\n\n\n\n> **Website workflow note.**\n> This page reflects the current exported API and recommended wrapper-first usage.\n> Last updated: **2026-02-19**.\n>\n> For the full package narrative, see the main package vignettes (basic, unconditional, conditional, and causal).\n\n\n# Causal Inference: Mixed Backends (CRP+SB) {#causal-mixed-backends}\n\nThis vignette fits two causal models using different backends and kernels:\n\n- Model A: CRP bulk-only (Cauchy)\n- Model B: SB with GPD tail (Laplace)\n\nEach model demonstrates the full causal S3 workflow: bundle, fit, predict, plot, ATE, and QTE.\n\n## What youâ€™ll learn\n\n- How backend choice (CRP vs SB) and tail choice (`GPD = FALSE/TRUE`) affect predictive uncertainty and downstream causal estimands.\n- How to keep comparisons interpretable by using the same post-fit S3 surface across models (`summary()`, `predict()`, `plot()`).\n- How to read both mean and quantile effect summaries and treat them as model-based functionals.\n## When to use this template\n\n- You want an apples-to-apples comparison of causal models that differ by **backend** and/or **tail augmentation**.\n- You want a compact example of the full causal S3 workflow in one place.\n## Next steps\n\n- Use the â€śsame-backendâ€ť causal examples to isolate tail effects from backend effects.\n---\n\n## Data Setup\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\ndata(\"causal_alt_real500_p4_k2\")\ny <- causal_alt_real500_p4_k2$y\nA <- causal_alt_real500_p4_k2$A\nX <- as.matrix(causal_alt_real500_p4_k2$X)\n\nsummary_tbl <- tibble(\n  statistic = c(\"N\", \"Mean\", \"SD\", \"Min\", \"Max\"),\n  value = c(length(y), mean(y), sd(y), min(y), max(y))\n)\n\nsummary_tbl\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n# A tibble: 5 Ă— 2\n  statistic   value\n  <chr>       <dbl>\n1 N         500    \n2 Mean        0.274\n3 SD          1.76 \n4 Min        -8.09 \n5 Max         5.27 \n```\n\n\n:::\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nx_eval <- X[1:40, , drop = FALSE]\ny_eval <- y[1:40]\nu_threshold <- as.numeric(stats::quantile(y, 0.8, names = FALSE))\n```\n:::\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\ndf_causal <- data.frame(y = y, A = as.factor(A), x1 = X[, 1], x2 = X[, 2])\n\np_scatter <- ggplot(df_causal, aes(x = x1, y = y, color = A)) +\n  geom_point(alpha = 0.5) +\n  labs(title = \"Outcome vs X1 by Treatment\", newdata =\"X1\", y = \"y\", color = \"Treatment\") +\n  theme_minimal()\n\np_scatter\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](ex11-causal-same-backend-crp_files/figure-html/data-scatter-1.png){width=768}\n:::\n:::\n\n\n---\n\n## Model A: CRP Bulk-only (Cauchy)\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nbundle_crp_bulk <- bundle(\n  x = y,\n  treat = A,\n  X = X,\n  kernel = \"cauchy\",\n  backend = \"crp\",\n  PS = \"logit\",\n  GPD = FALSE,\n  components = 5,\n  mcmc_outcome = list(niter = 400, nburnin = 100, nchains = 1, thin = 2, seed = 1),\n  mcmc_ps = list(niter = 400, nburnin = 100, nchains = 1, thin = 2, seed = 1)\n)\n\nbundle_crp_bulk\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\nCausalMixGPD causal bundle\nPS model: Bayesian logit (A | X) \n      Field                    Treated                    Control\n    Backend Chinese Restaurant Process Chinese Restaurant Process\n     Kernel                     cauchy                     cauchy\n Components                          5                          5\n   GPD tail                      FALSE                      FALSE\n    Epsilon                      0.025                      0.025\n\nOutcome PS included: TRUE \nn (control) = 232 | n (treated) = 268 \n```\n\n\n:::\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nsummary(bundle_crp_bulk)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\nCausalMixGPD causal bundle summary\nCausalMixGPD causal bundle\nPS model: Bayesian logit (A | X) \n      Field                    Treated                    Control\n    Backend Chinese Restaurant Process Chinese Restaurant Process\n     Kernel                     cauchy                     cauchy\n Components                          5                          5\n   GPD tail                      FALSE                      FALSE\n    Epsilon                      0.025                      0.025\n\nOutcome PS included: TRUE \nn (control) = 232 | n (treated) = 268 \n```\n\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nfit_crp_bulk <- load_or_fit(\n  \"ex11-causal-same-backend-crp-fit_crp_bulk\",\n  quiet_mcmc(dpmix.causal(bundle_crp_bulk))\n)\nsummary(fit_crp_bulk)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n-- PS fit --\nCausalMixGPD PS fit\nmodel: logit \n\n-- Outcome fits --\n[control]\nMixGPD fit | backend: Chinese Restaurant Process | kernel: Cauchy Distribution | GPD tail: FALSE\nn = 232 | components = 5 | epsilon = 0.025\nMCMC: niter=400, nburnin=100, thin=2, nchains=1 \nFit\nUse summary() for posterior summaries; plot() for diagnostics; predict() for predictions.\n\n[treated]\nMixGPD fit | backend: Chinese Restaurant Process | kernel: Cauchy Distribution | GPD tail: FALSE\nn = 268 | components = 5 | epsilon = 0.025\nMCMC: niter=400, nburnin=100, thin=2, nchains=1 \nFit\nUse summary() for posterior summaries; plot() for diagnostics; predict() for predictions.\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nparams(fit_crp_bulk)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\nPosterior mean parameters (causal)\n\n[treated]\nPosterior mean parameters\n\n$alpha\n[1] 0.4577\n\n$w\n[1] 0.5346 0.4449\n\n$location\n[1]  0.9282 -0.4337\n\n$scale\n[1] 0.6633 0.5094\n\n[control]\nPosterior mean parameters\n\n$alpha\n[1] 0.6085\n\n$w\n[1] 0.4127 0.3057 0.2317\n\n$location\n[1] -0.1074  0.6607 -0.1662\n\n$scale\n[1] 0.5233 0.4950 0.4293\n```\n\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nplot(fit_crp_bulk, family = c(\"traceplot\", \"autocorrelation\", \"running\"))\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n\n=== treated ===\n\n=== traceplot ===\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](ex11-causal-same-backend-crp_files/figure-html/plot-fit-crp-bulk-1.png){width=768}\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n\n=== autocorrelation ===\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](ex11-causal-same-backend-crp_files/figure-html/plot-fit-crp-bulk-2.png){width=768}\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n\n=== running ===\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](ex11-causal-same-backend-crp_files/figure-html/plot-fit-crp-bulk-3.png){width=768}\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n\n=== control ===\n\n=== traceplot ===\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](ex11-causal-same-backend-crp_files/figure-html/plot-fit-crp-bulk-4.png){width=768}\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n\n=== autocorrelation ===\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](ex11-causal-same-backend-crp_files/figure-html/plot-fit-crp-bulk-5.png){width=768}\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n\n=== running ===\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](ex11-causal-same-backend-crp_files/figure-html/plot-fit-crp-bulk-6.png){width=768}\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\npred_mean_bulk <- predict(fit_crp_bulk, newdata =x_eval, type = \"mean\",\n                          interval = \"credible\", nsim_mean = 100)\nhead(pred_mean_bulk)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n  id   estimate     lower     upper        ps\n1  1  0.7642320  7.847809 -1.233104 0.4525149\n2  2 -0.1588853 -4.487410  1.420477 0.6343279\n3  3  1.9215123  0.611024  8.659149 0.6385126\n4  4 -0.5687006 -5.568246  8.543622 0.5652830\n5  5  0.6058130 -3.067381  3.340523 0.4731408\n6  6 -2.5033268 -3.789321 -3.901392 0.5710738\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nplot(pred_mean_bulk)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](ex11-causal-same-backend-crp_files/figure-html/predict-mean-crp-bulk-1.png){width=768}\n:::\n\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](ex11-causal-same-backend-crp_files/figure-html/predict-mean-crp-bulk-2.png){width=768}\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\npred_q_bulk <- predict(fit_crp_bulk, newdata =x_eval, type = \"quantile\",\n                       p = 0.5, interval = \"credible\")\nhead(pred_q_bulk)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n  id index  estimate      lower     upper        ps\n1  1   0.5 0.4699805 0.03304969 0.8346934 0.4525149\n2  2   0.5 0.4699805 0.03304969 0.8346934 0.6343279\n3  3   0.5 0.4699805 0.03304969 0.8346934 0.6385126\n4  4   0.5 0.4699805 0.03304969 0.8346934 0.5652830\n5  5   0.5 0.4699805 0.03304969 0.8346934 0.4731408\n6  6   0.5 0.4699805 0.03304969 0.8346934 0.5710738\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nplot(pred_q_bulk)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](ex11-causal-same-backend-crp_files/figure-html/predict-quantile-crp-bulk-1.png){width=768}\n:::\n\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](ex11-causal-same-backend-crp_files/figure-html/predict-quantile-crp-bulk-2.png){width=768}\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\npred_d_bulk <- predict(fit_crp_bulk, newdata =x_eval, y = y_eval,\n                       type = \"density\", interval = \"credible\")\nhead(pred_d_bulk)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n  id          y        ps trt_estimate  trt_lower  trt_upper con_estimate\n1  1  0.8901906 0.4525149            1 0.15508016 0.24759799            1\n2  2 -1.3417565 0.6343279            2 0.12610960 0.21523565            2\n3  3  1.1375287 0.6385126            3 0.19758626 0.30855405            3\n4  4 -1.9223578 0.5652830            4 0.04779155 0.07941277            4\n5  5 -3.3339817 0.4731408            5 0.01355848 0.02061177            5\n6  6  0.9393979 0.5710738            6 0.16349298 0.26542488            6\n   con_lower  con_upper\n1 0.06210510 0.14302934\n2 0.16699071 0.34573927\n3 0.05296129 0.17038987\n4 0.05762851 0.11569214\n5 0.01209780 0.02345698\n6 0.05918913 0.14478865\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nplot(pred_d_bulk)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](ex11-causal-same-backend-crp_files/figure-html/predict-density-crp-bulk-1.png){width=768}\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\npred_surv_bulk <- predict(fit_crp_bulk, newdata =x_eval, y = y_eval,\n                          type = \"survival\", interval = \"credible\")\nhead(pred_surv_bulk)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n  id          y        ps trt_estimate trt_lower trt_upper con_estimate\n1  1  0.8901906 0.4525149            1 0.3648867 0.4519412            1\n2  2 -1.3417565 0.6343279            2 0.8087685 0.8720650            2\n3  3  1.1375287 0.6385126            3 0.3102570 0.3961727            3\n4  4 -1.9223578 0.5652830            4 0.8791320 0.9184353            4\n5  5 -3.3339817 0.4731408            5 0.9344207 0.9555599            5\n6  6  0.9393979 0.5710738            6 0.3542958 0.4407136            6\n  con_lower con_upper\n1 0.2405924 0.3768160\n2 0.7673511 0.8527106\n3 0.2114748 0.3484321\n4 0.8656183 0.9238178\n5 0.9343424 0.9628106\n6 0.2356072 0.3711956\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nplot(pred_surv_bulk)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](ex11-causal-same-backend-crp_files/figure-html/predict-survival-crp-bulk-1.png){width=768}\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nate_bulk <- ate(fit_crp_bulk, interval = \"credible\", nsim_mean = 100)\nhead(ate_bulk)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n$fit\n[1] 0.2318907\n\n$lower\n[1] -17.88207\n\n$upper\n[1] 15.77044\n\n$ate\n$ate$fit\n  id  estimate     lower    upper\n1  1 0.2318907 -17.88207 15.77044\n\n$ate$draws\n               [,1]\n  [1,]   3.03604188\n  [2,]   0.19981340\n  [3,]  -3.06294783\n  [4,]  -0.67513129\n  [5,] -31.44881406\n  [6,]   7.99285375\n  [7,]  -0.07729997\n  [8,]   2.91474265\n  [9,]  -0.59906593\n [10,]  -3.57468769\n [11,]  -8.07457844\n [12,]   0.81409938\n [13,]   2.13010099\n [14,]